<node id="&lt;hyperedge&gt;&quot;If a policy is issued to an insured person based on an incorrect age, the following may apply: - If the insured person is still eligible for insurance, the premium amount will be adjusted to the correct amount based on the correct date of birth at the insured person's effective date and; - If overpaid, we will refund the excess premiums calculated at the time a claim is made against this policy; or - If underpaid, we will decrease the benefit amount by the amount underpaid at the time a claim is made against this policy. - If the insured person is not eligible for insurance, all coverages under this policy will be considered never to have been in force and we will refund all premiums paid.&quot;">
